category: LITERARY HELPERS
category comment: 

clue: In "Casino Royale" she's described as "M's private secretary"

response: Miss Moneypenny

clue: Gandalf said to him, "You shall go away with Mr. Frodo!"

response: Samwise

clue: In this Cormac McCarthy novel John Grady Cole & his pal Rawlins are hired to tame some equines

response: All the Pretty Horses

clue: In this Wilde work Algernon's manservant is named Lane, while Jack has a butler named Merriman

response: The Importance of Being Earnest

clue: Frank helps Cora kill her hubby but is wrongly convicted of a murder he didn't commit in this James M. Cain novel

response: The Postman Always Rings Twice

